<br>
Mages aren't permitted to do more than CotH &amp; Rod.  This isn't some Draconian plot to keep mages down.  It's just that CotH/Rod are so much more valuable than anything else the mage can do that if the mage does do something else, it's obvious he's not pulling his weight even to him.  Also, if you take faction hits as a mage, you will have to lots of repair work after every raid or you won't be useful for CotH.  No CoTH means no raid for many spots due to the ridiculous time it takes slogging through junk spawns without it.  Do DD and you take faction hits again and you won't have mana for rods.  No rods often means raid wipe.  Summon pet and you just screwed up positioning (grat's on wipe again).<br>
<br>
Beastlords have even less utility on raids.  No pet permitted, pathetic damage output, only way to contibute is really via small 300hp patch heals, savagery, and spiritual purity.<br>
<br>
So, while pretty much any guild is happy to have mages, necros, and beastlords that like playing their class, most of those don't really like raid-play for their class.  It's vastly different from xp-play. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
