<br>
BTW, my comments about pets being generally forbidden is even after the pet changes.  Those changes don't really address pets on raids.  They make pets a lot safer in xp zones, but don't help much with the major pet concerns on big MOB kills.  The issues there are facing, positioning, and door-opening -- all of which are screwed up by pets (sometimes a little, sometimes to the point of a wipe).  Pets still don't respond to commands promptly, too.  I can't count the number of times I see &quot;backing off master&quot; while a pet continues to chase and attack.<br>
<br>
Basically, the relatively miniscule gain from a few pets on a MOB just plain isn't worth the risks.  BLs are a great xp class.  I love xp'ing with 'em, but they're the least desired of any class for raids. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
