<br>
For soloing, there are good levels that you blow through like nothing, and there and level where you get the junk kicked out of you.  Just depends on how recent your pet buff is.  For grouping, I often find myself slowing, occasional debuff or dot, and meleeing.  Yes, we do melee, and with pet up do a significant amount of damage.  Not rogue or monk level, perhaps, but significant.  Minor CC is good too, flash of light in wide open areas, or &quot;pet mezzing&quot; indoors.  On raids, we melee, and that's usually it.  So you're not the most needed class for huge mobs, oh well, you're in there meleeing.  On some raids, I do preslows, which usually works well being as I can take the hits slightly better than someone wearing a robe :P and at the high high end there are a few class specific spells that make us useful.  But, mostly, you just add damage.<br>
<br>
Ignore preconceptions about the class, there are a LOT of them out there.  Thankfully, people on FV are much more open than I hear some other servers are, I personally have not ever been turned down for a group or raid because of class.  If you do choose this route, and have questions, shoot me or one of the other beastlords a tell and we'll sort you out.  If not, good luck in Norrath.<br>
<br>
Oh, and to the person above saying no pets on raids:  if you aren't being allowed to use a pet, there better be a very good reason why.  If resists get fixed, some aoe problems may be solved, but even without, high end beastlord on eqbeastlord.com have said, repeatedly, that in 90% of all raids you will have a pet up. <p>-----------------------------<BR><A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438' target=new>Rhatha Sha`Naya</A> and Swiftclaw &lt;Chosen of Vah&gt;<BR>
