<br>
Beastlords are a fantastic xp class.  I love grouping with them.  They're inconsenquential on raids, though, even when they can use their pets.  This is not a preconception.  This is based on what I see raiding every day.  If I were to build a list of needed and desired classes for a raiding guild (ignoring friendships, etc), beastlords would be dead last.  I'd probably guild one or two out of pity, but that's about it.<br>
<br>
Please note that I'd never want to create a pure-raid guild that focused on raids to the complete exclusion of everything else, that's just an example.  My idea of an ideal guild has a good set of the core needed classes and lots of fun people playing whatever class works for them.  My current guild has a couple of great beastlords and I wouldn't trade them out.  I do pity them a bit for their class choice, though. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
